rComments: Gottheil isn't bad. Lectures are pointless & the only reason to show up is because he gives quizzes in them. Discussion is pointless don't go to it either. The class is easy. Just 1 midterm & a final. Not too hard because it's all short answer questions. He also curves the class a letter grade. Just buy, read,& learn from his book & you're good.

Terrible lecturer. Tells bad stories with too much detail that has nothing to do with the topics. Read the book and you will do okay on the tests, which are short answer. His tests are not really similar to the past, he's pretty dynamic in his teaching.Final is almost 50% of your grade so you basically need to do well on that

Funny how he was not able to cover economics of exchange rate in the end because of his long, monotonous stories that help little in furthering the understanding of the topic at hand but a lot in distracting you from  the lecture. Gotheil is aloof and unhelpful as well but succeeds completely in making a very interesting subject extremely dull.

I don't understand why everyone badmouths this guy so much. His class is easy. Midterm and final are short essay questions, pretty much one from each chapter, and very predictable. Sure he's a goofy old guy, but he's funny, his book is extremely clear, and the class doesn't require a whole lot of work to get an A. IMHO, Gottheil is pretty OK.

the thing that makes this class so hard is not gottheil, it is the TAs. none of them care very much, and to be honest, their might be one that speaks clear english each semester. gottheil is a good professor. he knows a lot about the subject and uses useful examples in the text and in class. read the book, do the vocab words, and youll do fine.

Not interested in teaching at all. Only reason he seems to drag himself to work is that by doing so he does a very good business of selling each semester 2000 plus books that he wrote himself. He changes the edition every year and makes sure that you waste 160 bucks on his book to learn stuff on your own that he is not gonna teach you.
Terrible class, none of the TAs spoke english, and Fred is one of the hardest graders ever. But there is not that much work to do.

I do not understand why so many people think Gottheil is a bad professor.  His lectures may be boring, but if you pay attention in them he goes over exactly what will be on the exams.  Just keep up with your reading and you will have an easy A.
Lectures were not helpful...at all

Sure, there is a book available but this is no University of Phoenix. It is one thing if a professor is not able to get his point across. It is quite another if he is not willing to try at all. I am sorry but when I am paying 20k+ for college, I expect my professors to be WILLING AND ABLE to teach. A disappointing professor thorough and thorough.

The class is not that difficult if you just read the book.  You don't have to go to lecture (although there are pop quizzes), but go to the TA sessions because they just review what he went over in lecture.  If you memorize definitions and graphs, the class isn't that difficult.

Honestly, I hated this class with a passion for a few reasons (mainly my fault). It's ALWAYS a morning class. The constant references to his brother's hat factory and the fish market are annoying and lectures are pointless aside from pop quizzes. However, I opened the book once and never studied and finished with a C somehow. HUGE curve.

I freaked out because I thought he was going to be extremely difficult. Upon taking the course I found out that he was pretty easy. Rumor has it that he was put on probation and that he now has to be more lenient to stupid answers. For those of you who actually study, it's not that hard to get an A. He's a nice man, misunderstood.
just remember all the vocabs, and you WILL get an A period

I am warning you under any circumstance.. try not to get this professor. You literally need to memorize the text book and even then its impossible. The final was worth 55% of our grade. This class will pull ur GPA down so far u'll probably cry. Avoid at all costs

Gottheil is infamous on U of I's campus as the WORST professor here. His tests are impossibly hard, a reason why his teaching career has been under review by the University for years. For a 100 level class, it will feel like a 400. Gottheil is a joke, do anything you can to avoid him.

Most boring and meaningless class ever! Attending class is only for the pop-quiz. There will be five, each counts for 1%. Make sure you are there in the last 10 minutes. Plus, read the textbook carefully. The midterm and final exam are all short answers. And there's no minus or plus, only A B C D for grade. Prevent this class if possible!

I fail to understand why so many people hate Gottheil. He has been an inspiration to me not only for his out-of-the-box, interesting lesssons, but also for the passion with which he teaches everyday. To see a financially well-off 70 something year old show up at 8am every day with the enthusiasm and dedication he shows is incredible.
Terrible. Enough said.
terrible.  obviously a very smart guy, but can't teach.  exams are impossible.  lecture was useless.
